This is an AE which is inflammation of small blood vessels (usually post-capillary venules in the dermis), characterized by palpable purpura and it is the most common vasculitis seen in clinical practice.
This is an AE which is a medical condition in which injury to the large or small intestine occurs due to not enough blood supply.

This is an AE which is a cutaneous condition that presents as slowly growing, multiple, discrete but grouped, red to violaceous papules.
This is an AE which constitutes a prevalent, chronic, and progressive retinal degenerative disease of the macula that affects elderly people and cause central vision impairment.

This is an AE which is the natural formation of new blood vessels (neo- + vascular + -ization), usually in the form of functional microvascular networks, capable of perfusion by red blood cells, that form to serve as collateral circulation in response to local poor perfusion or ischemia.
This is an AE which is a skin condition characterized by crops of small, tender, erythematous nodules on the legs, mostly on the calves and shins.
This is an AE which encompass a large and diverse group of underlying pathologies ranging from venous thromboembolism to congenital malformations to inflammatory vasculitides.
This is an AE which encompasses inflammation in the pulmonary vasculature with involved vessels varying in caliber from large elastic arteries to capillaries.
This is an AE which is a disease characterized by a weeks-long course of thunderclap headaches, sometimes focal neurologic signs, and occasionally seizures.

This is an AE which is a skin condition characterized by fixed urticarial lesions that appear histologically as a vasculitis.
This is an AE which is any of a range of lesions from a simple birthmark to a large tumor that may be disfiguring.

This is an AE which is an outdated term to describe certain types of headache which were thought to be related to blood vessel swelling and hyperemia as cause of pain.

This is an AE which is a blood vessel or lymph vessel abnormality. Vascular malformations are one of the classifications of vascular anomalies, the other grouping is vascular tumors.
This is an AE which is a tumor of vascular origin; a soft tissue growth that can be either benign or malignant, formed from blood vessels or lymph vessels.
This is an AE which is when there is a local hematoma being contained by the surrounding tissue around an vascular artery.
This is an AE which is a condition of red or purple discolored spots on the skin that do not blanch on applying pressure.
This is an AE which is a change of the human skin which affects its color, appearance, or texture and causes by vascular disease.

This is an AE which is excess accumulation of fluid (edema) in the intracellular or extracellular spaces of the vasogenic brain.
This is an AE which is inflammation of the inner part of the nose that is not caused by an allergy.
This is an AE which is a postperfusion syndrome characterized by low systemic vascular resistance and a high cardiac output.
This is an AE which  refers to a condition in which an arterial spasm leads to vasoconstriction.
This is an AE which is a type of arrhythmia.

This is an AE which is a device used in neurosurgery to treat hydrocephalus and relieve elevated intracranial pressure when the normal flow of cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) inside the brain is obstructed.
This is an AE which refers to a condition where the left atrium or right atrium of the heart is larger than would be expected. It can also affect both atria.

This is an AE which is a set of manifestations caused by the failure of the heart's function as a pump supporting the blood flow through the body; its signs and symptoms result from a structural and/or functional abnormality of the heart, that disrupts its filling with blood or its ejecting of it during each heart beat.
This is an AE which is an arrhythmia, more specifically a tachycardia affecting the ventricles with a rate over 250-350 beats/min, and one of the most indiscernible.
This is an AE which is thickening of the walls of a ventricle (lower chamber) of the heart.
This is an AE which is one of the classifications of movement disorders causes by ventricular disease, and refers to decreased bodily movement .
This is an AE which is a defect in the ventricular septum, the wall dividing the left and right ventricles of the heart.
This is an AE which consists of multiple, radially oriented dilated medullary veins that drain into a transparenchymal venous stem.
This is an AE which is a group of disorders that destroy blood vessels by inflammation caused by viral.
